Purpose: To create a positive and inclusive environment for the project team.

Expected Behavior:
Respect: Be kind and respectful to everyone.
Inclusivity: Make sure everyone feels welcome and valued.
Professionalism: Act professionally in all interactions.

Unacceptable Behavior:
Harassment: No offensive comments, threats, or unwelcome attention.
Discrimination: No discrimination based on race, gender, sexual orientation, disability, etc.
Disruption: Avoid behavior that disrupts the project.

Reporting and Enforcement:
Reporting: Clear instructions on how to report issues.
Confidentiality: Keep reports confidential.
Consequences: Possible actions include warnings or removal from the project.

Acknowledgment:
Agreement: All team members must agree to follow the Code of Conduct.
Updates: Team members will be informed of any changes.
